1
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:07,860
Hey, I'm out at a ravine.

2
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:09,620
What's this thing that spans across it?

3
00:00:09,969 --> 00:00:12,240
That is how you get to my sector.

4
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:13,860
No kidding.

5
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:15,180
Well, let me hike over.

6
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:17,640
Well, it's locked up in mainly for
emergencies.

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:19,680
I've never actually used it.

8
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,200
Rangers use it from time to time,
but that's it.

9
00:00:24,820 --> 00:00:25,260
Help!

10
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:26,100
Oh, God!

11
00:00:26,101 --> 00:00:27,101
It's an emergency!

12
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:28,900
Oh, really?

13
00:00:30,050 --> 00:00:32,520
Yeah, I got eyes on a tornado!

14
00:00:32,521 --> 00:00:33,700
I gotta get out of here!

15
00:00:34,474 --> 00:00:36,500
A tornado in the heart of the Rockies?

16
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:38,140
Yes!

17
00:00:38,980 --> 00:00:40,980
Holy moly, I need to call this in!

18
00:00:41,439 --> 00:00:42,940
Tom, Two Forks sees a tornado.

19
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,040
He says he needs an evac into my sector.

20
00:00:45,429 --> 00:00:47,360
It's a meteorological impossibility?

21
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:48,849
There haven't been
tornadoes in the Greater

22
00:00:48,850 --> 00:00:51,061
Yellowstone Region in
a hundred million years?!

23
00:00:51,085 --> 00:00:55,195
You´re going to need him to stay and take a detailed personal account even if it means giving his life?

24
00:00:55,219 --> 00:00:57,319
Okay, I´II tell him!

25
00:00:58,179 --> 00:00:59,250
Sorry, Hank.

26
00:00:59,490 --> 00:01:00,490
No dice.

27
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:02,830
Man...

